      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six. This high-revving powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is routed through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to the rear wheels via a factory M-Variable differential lock. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a recent suspension refresh and documented subframe reinforcement\u2014a critical preventative measure for this platform. While showing minor patina consistent with its mileage, the mechanical integrity is prioritized; recent rod bearing replacement and valve adjustments have been completed to ensure peak volumetric efficiency. Riding on staggered Style 67 forged alloys, this M3 offers the raw, analog feedback and telepathic steering rack sought by purists.",
